The Digentia, now the Licenza, was a stream formed by the Fons Bandusia, and running near the poet's abode through the territory of Mandela, a small Sabine village in the vicinity.—-105. Sed satis est orare Jovem, quae donat et aufert,&c. Horace distinguishes between the things we ought to hope for from the gods, and those we are to expect only from ourselves. Life and riches depend, according to the poet, upon the pleasure of Jove, but an equal mind upon our own exertions. .
